.TH "git alias.rebasefrom(1) User manual" "" "April, 2020" "" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
git rebasefrom
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
git rebasefrom branch - stow working copy, rebase first argument onto
HEAD, then unstow
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
git rebasefrom is a helper alias to rebase another branch onto HEAD.
.IP "1." 3
Ensures that the current HEAD is not a detached HEAD
.IP "2." 3
Ensures that the proper number of arguments have been provided
.IP "3." 3
Stores the ref of HEAD so it can be returned to later
.IP "4." 3
Ensures that the provided argument is associated with a branch
.IP "5." 3
Calls the stow alias to temporarily store the Workspace
.IP "6." 3
Checks out the source branch
.IP "7." 3
Calls the rebcombine alias to repeatedly merge changesets
.IP "8." 3
Checks out the previous HEAD
.IP "9." 3
Calls the unstow alias to restore the Workspace to its former condition
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
git rebasefrom branch
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
rebaseto finishfrom mergefrom
.SH DETAILS
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
rebasefrom = \[dq]!f() { : git man rebasefrom; \[rs]
    if ! git symbolic-ref HEAD; then echo \[aq]on detached head\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    [ $# -ne 1 ] && echo \[aq]Usage: rebasefrom branch\[aq] && return 1; \[rs]
    PREV=$(git symbolic-ref HEAD | cut -d/ -f3-); \[rs]
    if ! git show-ref $1; then echo \[aq]branch not a named ref\[aq]; return 1; fi; \[rs]
    if ! git stow; then return 1; fi; \[rs]
    git checkout $1; \[rs]
    git rebcombine $PREV; \[rs]
    git checkout $PREV; \[rs]
    git unstow; \[rs]
}; f\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
